NAME

    Win32::Mock - Mock Win32 modules


DESCRIPTION

    Win32::Mock provides mocked version of Win32 modules and functions so
    programs and modules with Win32 specific code can be tested on any
    operating system.


INSTALLATION

    To install this module, run the following commands:

        perl Makefile.PL
        make
        make test
        make install

    Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the 
    following commands:

        perl Build.PL
        ./Build
        ./Build test
        ./Build install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

    After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the 
    perldoc command.

        perldoc Win32::Mock

    You can also look for information at:

        Search CPAN
            http://search.cpan.org/dist/Win32-Mock

        CPAN Request Tracker:
            http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Win32-Mock

        AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
            http://annocpan.org/dist/Win32-Mock

        CPAN Ratings:
            http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Win32-Mock


